    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\n\"implicitly duplicates current buffer\", that's an unexpected behavior to me, sometime that would leads to unawared buffer leaks (api.nvim_buf_set_name does not return the duplicated buffer).\r\nas nvim_buf_set_name is a released api, i want to propose adding new rename api without this side effect.\r\n\r\nthat's what i observed:\r\n```\r\nlocal api = vim.api\r\n\r\nlocal bufnr = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\nprint(\"1\", \"bufname\", api.nvim_buf_get_name(bufnr), \"bufs\", vim.inspect(api.nvim_list_bufs()))\r\n\r\napi.nvim_buf_set_name(bufnr, \"hello\")\r\nprint(\"2\", \"bufname\", api.nvim_buf_get_name(bufnr), \"bufs\", vim.inspect(api.nvim_list_bufs()))\r\n\r\napi.nvim_buf_set_name(bufnr, \"world\")\r\nprint(\"3\", \"bufname\", api.nvim_buf_get_name(bufnr), \"bufs\", vim.inspect(api.nvim_list_bufs()))\r\n\r\napi.nvim_buf_set_name(bufnr, \"\")\r\nprint(\"4\", \"bufname\", api.nvim_buf_get_name(bufnr), \"bufs\", vim.inspect(api.nvim_list_bufs()))\r\n\r\napi.nvim_buf_set_name(bufnr, \"!\")\r\nprint(\"5\", \"bufname\", api.nvim_buf_get_name(bufnr), \"bufs\", vim.inspect(api.nvim_list_bufs()))\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n1 bufname  bufs { 1, 2 }\r\n2 bufname hello bufs { 1, 2 }\r\n3 bufname world bufs { 1, 2, 3 }\r\n4 bufname  bufs { 1, 2, 3, 4 }\r\n5 bufname ! bufs { 1, 2, 3, 4 }\r\n```\r\n\r\nmy usecase is that: say i have a plugin, it will reuse just one\r\nbuffer for all it's functionalities, but this buffer's name would be changed during the\r\nplugin's state changing: `shape://square -> shape://triangle -> shape://circle ...`\r\n\r\ni do want to reuse this buffer, as creating it may not be a cheap operation in some scenarios. and i dont have to delete the old buffer and create new buffer and do nvim_buf_set_name against the new buffer",
