            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`nvim_buf_set_name` is an old API. We wouldn't add `nvim_buf_set_name_no_duplicate` of course, but perhaps add an optional parameter to `nvim_buf_set_name2`.\r\n\r\n> my usecase is ... i have a plugin, it will reuse just one buffer for all it's functionalities, but this buffer's name would be changed during the plugin's state changing: `shape://square -> shape://triangle -> shape://circle ...`\r\n> \r\n> i do want to reuse this buffer, as creating it may not be a cheap operation in some scenarios. and i dont have to delete the old buffer and create new buffer and do nvim_buf_set_name against the new buffer\r\n\r\n`:file <new name>` (the standard way of \"renaming\" a buffer) also creates a new buffer. Both `nvim_buf_set_name`  and `ex_file` are just wrappers of `rename_buffer`.\r\n",
